		<description>My two cents, just give up. Just like junk mail, spam is inevitable, and unfortunately a part of life :(

If you want to make things more difficult though, you could have a contact page, and a very easy machine-human test in order to get to the page with your email aggress, something like &quot;Click the green square to send me a message&quot; which could link to a perl script to either redirect to a mailto: link or a &quot;Try again&quot; page. If this were done with an old-school img map, the robot would need to hit the correct coordinates to spider the contact page... Just thoughts.</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>My two cents, just give up. Just like junk mail, spam is inevitable, and unfortunately a part of life <img src='http://markos.gaivo.net/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif' alt=':(' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>If you want to make things more difficult though, you could have a contact page, and a very easy machine-human test in order to get to the page with your email aggress, something like &#8220;Click the green square to send me a message&#8221; which could link to a perl script to either redirect to a mailto: link or a &#8220;Try again&#8221; page. If this were done with an old-school img map, the robot would need to hit the correct coordinates to spider the contact page&#8230; Just thoughts.</p>
