		<description>Separate contacts page isn&#039;t always a solution and even when it is, it&#039;s not really a nice one, since at best it means nothing will get indexed.

You can see a weird, but readable representation of my email address (on my homepage) if you turn off Javascript. I use Javascript because the difficulty of emailing someone is inversely proportional to the number of people who&#039;ll do so.</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Separate contacts page isn&#8217;t always a solution and even when it is, it&#8217;s not really a nice one, since at best it means nothing will get indexed.</p>
<p>You can see a weird, but readable representation of my email address (on my homepage) if you turn off Javascript. I use Javascript because the difficulty of emailing someone is inversely proportional to the number of people who&#8217;ll do so.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
